This made me emotional to make

I saw this trend about somewhere between then and now, and loved it - when I first decided that I was going to heal my body and drop my restrictions around food, it was the hardest thing.

I started with small changes and small wins but they felt large and difficult at the time.

But eventually over time (and now years) I have expanded so much that oftentimes I forget how hard it was for me, since now I don’t think about food nearly as much as I used to. 

We often forget the little moments but the little moments are where the growth actually happened. 

Each and every choice—

to choose bread over a rice cake, a cappuccino over black coffee and real pasta over lentil pasta…

has led me to where I am today. 

For those who need to hear this - just start. Your future self will thank you 🤍

My current read @jenatkinhair book:

I love what she says about how with all the posts where everyone is “killing it” and “go go go,” we forget to acknowledge that the work it takes to find success can be exhausting. 

She says, “instead of glorifying the hustle, I wish we’d talk about it for what it is and acknowledge that as a culture, especially in America, we have a messed up view of the “business of busyness.” Being a workaholic should not be an aspiration even though a lot of people I know identify with that label and take some kind of pride in it.”

One of the more important posts I’ve made❤️

Take everything you see on social media with a grain of salt. What works for me may not work for you…

This is personally what helped me reverse my PCOS. Every book I read and social media post I came across told me to cut out dairy, gluten, and adhere to a plant-based diet.

For me, personally, that was the furthest thing to help me. In the last few years, I’ve incorporated quality proteins, dairy & gluten. 

Also monitoring my blood sugar which directly impacts hormones - I recommend @veristable thanks to @brigainz 

Above all, though, with PCOS and any hormone-related things, managing stress is #1.

This spicy salmon crispy rice was DELICIOUS!

Real ingredient pre-workouts:

• @frenchsquirrel.co Bateaux (dates are a slow-releasing carb w/ natural glucose for sustained energy + nut butter & cacao for healthy fats to provide blood sugar balance)

Chia seed pudding:
• 2 tbsp chia seeds
• 1/2 cup almond milk (I prefer coconut milk)
• 1 tbsp maple syrup
• cinnamon/pink salt
• optional protein powder - if so add more milk!

Stir to combine and refrigerate overnight. You can either add fruit the night before or the next morning 🐒

The first clip of me at a party at UCSB was my all time low - I had to get off the bull because I didn’t even have the energy to stay on 😕

I often get asked about how I healed my relationship with food, how I “did it.”

I don’t think there’s a destination or a place you get to completely, but it’s about every small decision you make.

For everyone “working on it” - it’s actually about working on it. Actions over words always! 

I kept saying I was working on it, but I was all talk until I actually took a bite of cake, ate the bread at the table, incorporated my fear foods slowly but surely.

The minute I prioritized my health and happiness over the number on the scale is when everything shifted. 

It wasn’t easy but all those bites have led me here. Tough advice but you gotta just do the damn thang! My DM’s are always open to chat 🫶🏼

Most people think that you can “spot” an eating disorder by just looking at someone.

What they don’t tell you about those struggling with food and exercise, is that it’s not a visible struggle *always*

The worst part in my experience was the mental space that was occupied by disordered thoughts and constant chatter.

After years of working through this, I had the brain space to start this account, begin cooking creatively again, run my business @frenchsquirrel.co, and most importantly, form connections with so many beautiful people through this platform and beyond…

Reminder to check in on those who don’t just “look too thin” too 💚

For a while I wasn’t able to pinpoint my deeper mission with creating @frenchsquirrel.co to the t.

I did an exercise on this and kept saying things like:

“Bringing healthy snacks for blood sugar balance to market”
“Hormone-friendly snacks”
“Fueling people’s bodies with real food and real chocolate”
“Health without a comprise on taste”

All of the above are true.

But I was encouraged to go deeper. What am I actually trying to do? What message am I actually trying to deliver?

After many meditative moments, I realized I created and continue to run @frenchsquirrel.co to help other people, especially women. 

to provide nourishing snacks to fuel their beautiful bodies and to remind them to be appreciative of the body they were given to walk this earth 🫶🏼

When I was struggling with food and exercise, that’s what I needed. So I’m passing it along to everyone I can ✨

MONDAY MANTRA 🤝

consistency > motivation 

Exercise, for me, is more of a habit/routine. It’s not motivation, but consistency… showing up is half of it 😊

High protein cottage cheese cheesecake with blueberry chia jam🫐

Recipe from @sannevloet @soulsyncbody 

Blended cottage cheese, 1 egg, 1 scoop vanilla protein, vanilla extract or paste, and salt!

Lined a ramekin with ghee and air fried it until brown on top.
Made the chia jam but combining frozen blueberries, chia seeds and maple syrup and let that thicken.

Top the cottage cheese cheesecake with the jam and if you have patience, refrigerate.

I wouldn’t have this every day because it definitely took more time but a great idea for a sweet high protein brekkie!

For everyone new here, I no longer put myself in this box of “health & wellness” because it looks different for everyone.

For me, that’s eating real food as much as I can, like nutrient-dense fruits, vegetables & high quality animal products…

AND enjoying smash burgers and chocolate chip cookies (some of my favorite things).

I also like exercising but not to the point where it takes up my entire life. I’ve formed a completely different relationship with the gym in the last 2 months alone - excited for the journey.

If you relate to any of the above, welcome 🫶🏼

• sesame

The actual bagels were fantastic, but I prefer a bagel sandwich. The dip style is fun every now and then, however the move would definitely be to take these to-go and make a sandwich at home with lox, tomato, cc and the works!

So if you’re able to do the above ^ then it’s worth it in my opinion 🥯 otherwise, I’d stick to a NYC bagel shop where they make the sandwich.

Creamiest dreamiest overnight oats using an almost empty peanut butter jar! My all time favorite breakfast hack 🙃🥜

Recipe:
1/3 cup overnight oats
1 tbsp chia seeds
1/4-1/3 cup greek yogurt
1 tbsp maple syrup
Sea salt & cinnamon 

Shake shake shake IT till the peanut butter gets all incorporated and refrigerate overnight 🤝

Serve with cacao nibs & fruit!

This is my version of girl dinner - simple, whole ingredients.

I used to waaaay overcomplicate my meals in an effort to be healthy, adding in so many different substitutes, powders, etc.

Pumpkin protein muffins have been on my mind 💭🎃

I love having an afternoon snack that has a good source protein so that I’m not grazing the whole day and these muffins are the perfect “une pause” moment.

Recipe below inspired by @eatthegains (adjust sweetness to your liking!):

1 cup rolled oats
1 cup pumpkin purée
1 cup Greek yogurt (I use @strausmilk)
2 eggs
1/2 packed up vanilla protein powder 
1/3 cup maple syrup 
1 tsp cinnamon
1 tbsp pumpkin pie spice
1 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda 
Pinch sea salt
1/2 cup dark chocolate chips

Blend all ingredients together besides the chocolate chips. Once blended, fold the chocolate in. Line a muffin tin with paper liners or avo oil spray. Bake at 350F for ~15-25 mins depending on your oven.

ENJOY!

Our beloved chocolate chip pumpkin bread 🫶🏼🎃

This was ELITE - one of the best desserts we’ve made!gluten-free, refined sugar free pumpkin loaf with chocolate chips & a homemade 3-ingredient cream cheese frosting!

We used @dadaeats recipe below 👇🏼 
1 1/4 cups almond flour, packed
1 1/4 cups gluten-free oat flour, packed I recommend store-bought for this recipe
1 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp pumpkin pie spice (sub cinnamon) bump up to 1 tsp for a stronger pumpkin pie flavor.
3/4 cup coconut sugar
1/4 cup maple syrup
1 cup pumpkin purée
3 tbsp olive oil
1/4 cup creamy peanut, cashew, or almond butter
2 eggs
chocolate chips 

Baked for 40 mins at 350F. 

For the cream cheese frosting, we blended cream cheese with maple syrup and a splash of vanilla bean paste (sweetness to your liking).

Cool before frosting 🎃
ENJOY!

This dessert has been on REPEAT 🔁

So easy, mouthwatering, vegan & gluten-free & made with 4 simple ingredients. Inspired by @dadaeats 🥜

In a bowl, combine

• 1 bag @fitjoy grain-free pretzels crushed up (can also use rice cakes here)
• 1/2 cup organic peanut butter
• 1/3 cup pure maple syrup

Mix and spread into a parchment paper lined brownie tin. Freeze for 10 mins and then add melted dark chocolate on top + sea salt flakes for a finishing touch 🍫 I’ve also topped them with @frenchsquirrel.co Bisous which is incredible!!

Freeze for a few hours and then slice into bars, squares, rectangles, whatever you prefer ☺️

SO GOOD. Thank me later 👅👅

Top with flakey sea salt & @frenchsquirrel.co Bisous for the perfect crunch 💋

Birthday month, I am ready ♏️

Tomorrow is a full circle day for me. I am launching a product that I actually thought would be my first.

Although it doesn’t sound “sexy,” @frenchsquirrel.co was born out of my eating disorder I developed in college.

2018: When I studied abroad in Bordeaux, I tried so hard to get out of it, but it is a long journey, like everything in life. Truth is, it took YEARS even after I decided I was ready to heal. If you struggle with this, you know that voice never goes away, you just develop the tools to make it quieter. My favorite hobby there (and everywhere else in the world) was to browse the grocery store aisles, specifically nut butters. 

September 2019: I was scared of so many foods, yet I so badly wanted to get out of the hole that is restriction. It was incredibly isolating. Senior year of college, I applied for a job @pressedjuicery intentionally to put myself exactly where I was uncomfortable. All the sweets, chocolate, and toppings scared me. 

End of 2019: I graduated @ucsantabarbara early and knew I wanted to start my own business. I thought I was going to make nut butters (see slide 5 for the original mockup hahaha). 

January 2020: I decide I want to deepen my yoga practice, which was part of showing my body love again, and slowing down from killing it running on the treadmill every single day. I find @kevinwathey on the third page of google, and call to tell him I want to come on his yoga retreat in Bali. Here was my first real effort to reconnect with myself and amazing humans like @debbiepopielyoga 🫶🏼 I brought the protein bites as a travel snack, which eventually became my work snack and first product, Berets, thanks to @vitoantoci my mentor who guided me. 

NOW (and my point that it does get better if you decide so)

November 2023: launch of the original concept only upleveled, because a lot of growth has happened in 3 years. And in style, I am leaving on my fourth yoga retreat with Kevin to Portugal next week 🧘🏼‍♀️

Excited to share more 🐿️

So when @jloshep texted me with a reservation, had to schlep to the East Side. And I always say this, but the East Side has the best food 💯

My thoughts:

• loved the old Italian ambiance, super comforting and not what I was expecting in the best way

• enjoyed the chopped salad but it wasn’t necessary - would replace with another menu item next time

Was it the best meal ever? No, probably because I’ve had different variations of similar foods in LA, but it was very delicious and I’d definitely go back. I’d say it lived up the hype for the overall experience ☺️❤️

When people ask me how I got started in the food business, here is my answer ☺️

I also get asked, “how did you find your passion?”

Reminder that your love and passions change with you and can take many evolutions to find.

Easy instant pot chili!!
I was craving this so had to make my own version 🤤

1 tablespoon olive oil
1 lb grass-fed ground beef
Salt & pepper to taste
1 yellow onion diced
2 tablespoons tomato paste
1 tablespoon chili powder
1 teaspoon ground paprika
1 teaspoon ground cumin
½ teaspoon dried oregano
½ cup beef broth
1 can black beans 
1 can diced tomatoes (14.5 oz can)
Corn if you have it!

Cooked the onions with the spices in one pan and the beef separately. Make sure the beef is browned and cooked through. Once onions and spices are cooked, add beef broth. To your instant pot, add the black beans, diced tomatoes, beef, onion mixture, and salt and pepper. Cook with high-pressure for 10 minutes.

Top with yogurt or sour cream, lime juice, and cilantro, if desired 💚 SO YUM!

10 favorite places I ate on my Australia trip!!🇦🇺🦘

Of course it’s a whole country but breaking it down by my top things I ate.

In no particular order:

2. @the.pantry.melbourne - in Brighton, cute ambiance & they had a mix of foods. I liked their sushi bowl & set with miso soup. 

3. @supernormal_180 - probably one of the top meals we had all trip. Incredible creativity, so delicious. The dumplings and Korean rice cakes were insane. 

4. @tipo_00 - intimate pasta bar with fresh handmade pasta. Loved the meat pasta & tiramisu.

5. @highergroundmelbourne - best breakfast we had all trip. The chili scrambled eggs on roti and the pancakes >> loved the ambiance and high ceilings too 

6. @themezclub - @anna_rooke recommended, Byron Bay didn’t have the best dinner food but we really liked this place, specifically the chicken tagine.

7. @bayleafcafe - I liked the island energy and coconut cream cold brew + yogurt paleo granola bowl. Banana bread was yum too.

8. @frankiesgelato - this gelato hit the spot. Chocolate & salted caramel 👅

9. @threeblueducks - the most farm-to-table it can get, real ingredients 100% chemical free. 12-hour slow cooked brisket and potatoes were amazing. Loved the chocolate mousse too.

10. @_donnachang Dan Dan noodles with beef & peanuts was so cozy and flavorful. YUM!

Had to say it 🤝

I fell trap to this internet advice when I was beginning my health journey many years ago.

It sent me down a dark hole of information that didn’t serve me or my body well. 

These extreme habits caused many health issues for me, including losing my period for many years, digestion issues, hormone imbalances, low energy, PCOS, and more. 

You know your body best.
Don’t let random people on the internet & social media tell you what to eat, when and how to exercise, etc. 

Of course inspiration is one thing (and I love those motivational videos don’t get me wrong), BUT take what you need and leave what you don’t. 

& my DM’s are always open for any support 🤍
